Quote:  <i>Siestaing </i>: The verb, `to siesta', comes from the Spanish and means to take well-earned repose, preferably for as long as possible. It is now understood to embrace all periods during which the soldier is officially doing nothing but when he is probably doing down all and sundry.
Notes: (Johnny Euzed)
